> Just to add that from the perspective of flooding (+ associated impacts on
> health) a map of open drains would obviously be relevant. To be useful, though,
> it would probably need to be paired with a high-resolution DEM and probably
> some information about channel geometry (although this is probably quite
> standardised). I believe it's possible to extract a DEM from Worldview data
> (which I think we have?), although we would need some ground control points.
>
> There is some anecdotal evidence that improper waste management has caused
> localised flooding in Accra. As you would have seen, open drains tend to
> collect litter which can eventually cause a blockage and lead to flooding.
> Perhaps an interesting research topic would be to explore the extent to which
> we can predict (based on particular neighbourhood features) the likelihood of
> drain blockages.
>
> In summary, this could be interesting from the point of view of the water
> package, so I would be grateful to be kept in the loop as you move forward!
